links.description:
If you are using our JS or Ruby client you can use the `uploadFile` helper, passing either an URL or a local file as the argument.

To create a new upload without a client you will need to perform three separate steps.

1. Send a `POST` request to the `/upload-requests` endpoint, to retrieve an uploading URL;
2. Use the obtained URL to perform a `PUT` request, passing your file as payload;
3. Make a `POST` request to `/uploads` with the upload path, alt and title.

js.request:
const { SiteClient } = require("datocms-client").SiteClient;
const client = new SiteClient("YOUR-API-KEY");

// upload using URL:

client
  .uploadFile("http://i.giphy.com/NXOF5rlaSXdAc.gif")
  .then(uploadId => console.log(uploadId))
  .catch(error => console.log(error));

// or using local files:

client
  .uploadFile("./image.png")
  .then(uploadId => console.log(uploadId))
  .catch(error => console.log(error));
